  "content": [
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "What do you do",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "...when someone misses an appointment?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "…when someone cuts you off in traffic?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "…when someone is being careless?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Do you assume the worst—that",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "this",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "person is belligerent, stupid or dishonest? When they tell you their story--why they acted that way—do you try to assess whether you believe them, or if their explanation warrants concern or care?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Or—and it’s a very big or—do you simply give them the benefit of the doubt. Or at least consider the possibility that maybe:",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "listItem": "bullet",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "they made an honest mistake",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "listItem": "bullet",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "it’s an emergency, or",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "listItem": "bullet",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "they’re having a really bad day",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "It seems to me that regularly giving people a second chance is a far better approach to live by than assuming and looking for the worst in people, all the time.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Because, frankly, it doesn’t matter if you’re right or you’re wrong. It doesn’t matter if the people you come across are negligent or unprincipled or just plain human.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "What matters is the story you tell yourself. How it makes you",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "feel",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": ". And all the possibilities—the opportunities—that can only happen when you’re willing to invariably give people the benefit of the doubt.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}